  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Afghanistan: Supporting Access to Justice in Afghanistan (SAJA)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To improve the quality of legal aid services offered to the poor and disempowered. 2) To increase the effectiveness of the Elimination of Violence Against Women (EVAW) Units in the Attorney General&apos;s Office in prosecuting violence against women cases. 3) To improve the capacity of the Women&#x2019;s Protection Centers to implement better services to address beneficiaries&#x2019; needs. 4) To increase awareness of women&apos;s rights, legal rights, and access to justice for target beneficiaries.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: The Afghanistan Legal Aid and Advocates Network, the Ministry of Justice and the Afghanistan Independent Bar Association.
Indirect beneficiaries: Recipients of legal aid services, particularly the indigent, marginalized and disempowered.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aimed to improve access to, and quality of, legal and protective services for disempowered and survivors of gender-based violence in Afghanistan.</narrative>
  </description>
